The proposal dorley, T. The proposal for sanction of the tap water supply scheme has been submitted by the CEO, Zilla Parishad, Yavatmal for Government approval under Reference No. 5 as the per capita cost of the tap water supply scheme of Jari Jamani, Zila Yavatmal is more than the prescribed criteria.

The proposal for the present tap water supply scheme has been granted technical approval by the Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zilla Parishad, Yavatmal dated 4.5.2023. The Technical Scrutiny Committee, headed by Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad, Yavatmal, also met. The approval has been given in the meeting on 3.5.2023. The per capita cost of the scheme is Rs. 13,625 / -; the proposal for the scheme has been received through the District Water and Sanitation Mission with the prior approval of the Government as it exceeds the governance criteria. Jari Jamani, Dist. Yavatmal Tap Water Supply Scheme Rs. 49,77,000 - It was under the consideration of the government to grant administrative approval under the Jal Jeevan Mission programme for a budget of this value.

Government Decision In view of the facts mentioned in the foregoing Preamble, Md. Dolly Ta. The Jari Jamani District Yavatmal Tap Water Supply Scheme with a capacity of 55 litres per capita per day is being implemented at a cost of Rs. 13,625 / - per capita for tap water supply scheme at a cost of Rs. 49,77,000 - (Characters Rs. Nineteen and a half lakh seventy seven thousand only) is being given administrative approval under the Jal Jeevan Mission programme subject to fulfilment of the following terms and conditions: 1. The scheme should be implemented by the Zilla Parishad, Yavatmal. The Gram Panchayat concerned shall be responsible for taking over the scheme within 1 month from the date of receipt of intimation from the Executive Engineer concerned that the scheme has actually been completed after the implementation of the scheme. On actual completion of the scheme, a joint inspection of the scheme should be conducted by the concerned Executive Engineer, Maharashtra Jeevan Authority / Zilla Parishad and concerned Gram Panchayat officials and if any defects are found in such inspection, they should be rectified before handing over the scheme.
Government Decision No: Jajimi-2023 / Q. 14 3 / Papu-13

The contractor will be obligated to run the scheme for at least 9 years. The Zilla Parishad should ensure that the scheme is successfully completed. It also provides for maintenance repairs to the project. Follow the guidelines in the Government Decision dated 17th October, 2014.

Even if the scheme is implemented and the contractor runs the scheme for at least 9 years, the villagers should be able to recover the water bill for even this one year. The collected water supply should be given to the organization running the scheme.

Reference No. As per the provisions of the Government Decision dated 1st September, 2020 and the guidelines of the Central Government's Jal Jeevan Mission, 10% of the cost of the scheme shall be required to be retained with the Gram Panchayat as public share for maintenance of the water supply scheme. The Gram Panchayat and Zilla Parishad will be responsible for collecting this amount.

4) The scheme requires every household to be provided with a tap connection. To this end, 115 systems are required to record information about the given tap connections and forwarding tap connections so far. The Gram Panchayats concerned will be responsible for the necessary planning regarding the new connection.
The work of the scheme should be done by inviting e-tendering in the prescribed manner.
The land acquisition and all other permissions required for the scheme should be obtained within the prescribed time.
In order to ensure that the scheme is not used on a seasonal basis, the Gram Panchayat should ensure that the existing scheme in the village covered under the scheme is not implemented.

In order to meet the cost of operation and maintenance of the scheme, the concerned Gram Panchayat shall fix the water tariff for household, non-household and institutional tap connection holder as mentioned in the proposal for implementation of the scheme and increase it from time to time. Also, it will be mandatory for the Gram Panchayat to determine the water table required for the scheme to be self-sufficient and flood it as per the requirement, the officials of Maharashtra Jeevan Authority should clearly inform the villagers in detail in the Gram Sabha and only then start the work of the scheme.

10) 20% of the recovered waterbags should be kept with the implementing agency for major maintenance repairs. The plan pipes should be repaired every 5 years and the other pipes should be repaired every 3 years.

11) No assistance / grant shall be provided by the Government to the concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad / Maharashtra Jeevan Authority for meeting the recurring expenditure incurred every year for "operation, maintenance and maintenance of the scheme," depreciation in the scheme or renovation of machinery.
12) Ensure that the villages under the scheme are open defecation free but will always remain open defecation free.
43) No additional subsidy will be provided by the Government in case of any cost overrun of the scheme.
14) The conditions in the order of technical approval of the scheme should be fulfilled. Also referred to as No. The provision in the Government Decision 1 to 4 should be strictly adhered to.

15) As per the Government decision issued from time to time regarding Third Technical Examination of the Scheme by the Government, it shall be mandatory to conduct Third Technical Examination of the Scheme.
